				Well, this spell has been a life saver when hunting in Infected Paw.  Since often there are trains, and tanks *STILL* don't get that they shouldn't touch mezzed mobs, it's an easy way to keep them off the mob that's mezzed, and on the one that is thinking strait and wanting to beat the living daylights out of them.  On the flip side, like in the post below, it's a great way to make a warrior shape up if he's doing a bad job in the group /em grins mischievously :-)<BR>
