			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				okay this spell and the ones like it are, in theory, quite powerful. ive exparimented with them, and found that they have very short durations, but the effect is nice. you can, in a nutshell, make someone or something get more agro than it normally would. e.i. taunting would be more successful. it makes it easier to get the mob off *you*. calming visage can be casted in just the opposite effect, reducing the agro someone or something takes. e.i. that wizzie over there could theoretically safely nuke without as much worry of mob retaliation. this also allows the chanter to &quot;move&quot; the damage around the party. makin the mob not attack the main tank thats low on hp, and make it attack the backup while the main heals up. my personal favorite use for it would be if someone in the group is either not doing thier job, being a dick, or just pissing me off. i can simply make it so the mob 'likes' him/her a little more than the others. &gt;:)<BR>
im NOT sayin that all this is written in stone, but so far its worked with some consistency. any further opinions/comments are greatly appreciated. i hope ive been of some help.<BR>
<BR>
Virgis Mindreaper enchanter of the Luclin server<BR>
proud member of Misfits of Carnage<BR>
Drink up misfits, the fight will be long and hard!
				</font>
			</td>

